# Rule: ń”üblind_write
# Token: ń”üblind_write
# Priority: P0 (HIGHEST)
# Source: NeuronFS Governance Defaults

ń”üblind_write Õ┐ģvorq

FORBIDDEN: Writing code without reading existing file first
REASON: Blind writes can corrupt, misalign, or duplicate code

REQUIRED SEQUENCE:
    1. Read existing file with file read tool
    2. Understand current structure
    3. Make targeted edits (use patch, not overwrite)
    4. Verify edit was applied correctly

EXAMPLE VIOLATION:
    write_file("app.py", new_content)  # Without reading first ŌØī
    echo "code" > app.py               # Without checking existing ŌØī

CORRECT:
    content = read_file("app.py")
    patch("app.py", old_string, new_string)  # Ō£ģ

